不  但这是你上次和他谈话后
No, but it's the first time he's contacted

85
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,110
他第一次与谢泼德家族
anyone connected with the Shepherds

86
00:08:11,410 --> 00:08:12,980
有关的人联络
since you last spoke to him.

87
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:18,630
如果他这么想被抓的话  那就抓住他
Well, if he's trying to get caught, let's catch him.

88
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:26,050
邓肯·谢泼德到底会不会去作证
So is Duncan Shepherd testifying or not?

89
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:28,140
他的律师还在谈条件
His lawyers are negotiating the terms.

90
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:30,460
他们希望他能不公开作证
They're hoping that he could meet behind closed doors.

91
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,720
那他必须得被传唤
Well, then he needs to be subpoenaed.

92
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,130
我们会见过的每个议员
Every congressperson we've spoken to

93
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:36,430
-都同意如此  但是  -他们在拖延
- agrees he should be and yet-- - They're delaying.

94
00:08:36,430 --> 00:08:37,650
他们并不真想
I mean, there's no real desire

95
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:39,520
推动针对应用的调查
to move this app investigation along.

96
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,800
他们想保护自己人
They're protecting their own.

97
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,810
是众议院要求举行听证会的
The House asked for these hearings.

98
00:08:43,810 --> 00:08:45,600
他们需要走过场
The theatre is good for them.

99
00:08:45,890 --> 00:08:47,550
但我们在跟委员会的
But we are in constant contact

100
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:49,540
民主党成员密切联系  女士
with the Democratic members of the committee, ma'am.

101
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:50,670
给他们压力
They're feeling the pressure.

102
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,870
显然压力还不够
Well, clearly, not enough.

103
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,760
我们可以先逮捕几个议员
We can start arresting congresspeople.

104
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:55,680
有必要的话  把他们从众议院拉出来
Pull them out of the chambers if we have to.

105
00:08:55,690 --> 00:08:59,460
-举行听证会的意义  -是什么  打太极吗
- The whole point of the hearings-- - Is what? Obfuscation?

106
00:08:59,460 --> 00:09:02,470
怎么  这可是侵犯隐私的事
What? We're talking about invasion of privacy here.

107
00:09:02,470 --> 00:09:05,340
联邦检察官要证据确凿才肯
The US Attorney is resistant to pressing any kind of charges

108
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:08,240
-提出诉讼  -应用本身就是确凿证据
- without hard evidence. - The app is the evidence.

109
00:09:08,910 --> 00:09:11,560
-这就是起诉理由  诺拉  -也许吧
- This is grounds for prosecution, Nora. - Yes, maybe.

110
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:12,900
但联邦检察官不会同意
But the US Attorney would argue--

111
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,690
那就换掉联邦检察官
Replace the US Attorney.

112
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:18,930
这件事她拖了好几个月了
She's been dragging her feet on this for months.

113
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,530
女士  我们还得走正当程序
Ma'am, we still live in a world of due process.

114
00:09:22,610 --> 00:09:23,670
这会发出令人不安的信号
That would send a chilling message--

115
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:26,450
我们需要发出保护民主的信号
The message is we need to protect our democracy.

116
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:38,450
出于实际考虑  我们要取消今天的第四站行程
On a practical note, we're canceling the fourth stop today.

117
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:43,560
我们斟酌后觉得去了克利夫兰就不用去托莱多了
Upon reflection, we decided Toledo would be redundant with Cleveland.

118
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:45,650
帕姆  没事  不妨直说
Pam, it's fine. You can be honest.

119
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:47,760
三军统帅
The Commander In Chief

120
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:50,560
今天有些迷糊而已
