122
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,220
我们一到得梅因
When we touch down in Des Moines,

123
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:03,030
诺拉  你就可以直接回华府了
Nora, you can head straight back to DC.

124
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:19,040
斯克斯基  你是斯拉夫人吗
Is it Slavic, "Skorsky"?

125
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,700
我是波兰裔
Polish, in my case.

126
00:10:23,690 --> 00:10:24,740
你很孤独吧
You must be lonely.

127
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:30,700
我让记者团乘第二架飞机
I asked the press corps to take the second plane,

128
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:33,690
我们就好私下见面
so that you and I could meet privately.

129
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:37,460
四个月前  你见了两个人
Four months ago, you met with two people.

130
00:10:39,130 --> 00:10:43,050
现在一个人失踪了  一个人死了
One of them's missing and one of them is dead.

131
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:47,940
我最近总是遇到不幸
My life has certainly been punctuated with loss lately.

132
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:50,760
但也有运气
And just a bit of great luck.

133
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:52,670
但汤姆·汉默施密特就不走运了
Tom Hammerschmidt was not lucky.

134
00:10:53,310 --> 00:10:55,610
没错  确实很悲惨
No, he wasn't. That was tragic.

135
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:59,370
所以我觉得你该继承他的衣钵
That's why I think you should pick up his mantle.

136
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:03,100
完整地讲述弗兰西斯的政治生涯
And tell the full story of Francis' political career.

137
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,950
你在逗我吗
Are you messing with me?

138
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,170
不  我说真的
No. Far from it.

139
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,190
你调查并曝光了谢泼德自由基金会
You did a great job investigating and exposing

140
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,520
应用的事  这非常出色
the Shepherd Freedom Foundation app.

141
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:14,020
曝光其非法用途
Its nefarious uses.

142
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:18,280
我们不能让议员逍遥法外
We can't let congresspeople get away with things like that.

143
00:11:19,630 --> 00:11:21,720
我怀疑最高法院废了你之前
I wonder if you'll get them in line

144
00:11:21,730 --> 00:11:24,440
你能不能控制住他们
before the Supreme Court takes your power away.

145
00:11:27,050 --> 00:11:29,200
我和汤姆·汉默施密特最后一次谈话时
Tom Hammerschmidt and I, the last time we spoke,

146
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,760
谈到了我丈夫
we talked about my husband.

147
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:33,660
我希望可以跟你说完
And my hope is I could pick it up with you.

148
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,660
我有很多关于弗兰西斯的事要说
I have a lot that needs to be said about Francis,

149
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:38,450
他大大小小的罪过
his crimes and misdemeanors.

150
00:11:41,180 --> 00:11:42,880
你想不想听我说
You want my story or don't you?

151
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:50,220
又是轻微宫缩
Oh, it's these mini contractions.

152
00:11:50,220 --> 00:11:54,250
这叫希克斯假阵缩
They're, um... called Braxton Hicks.

153
00:11:54,650 --> 00:11:55,770
你有孩子吗
Do you have kids?

154
00:11:56,330 --> 00:11:57,650
没有
No, I don't.

155
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:01,490
这胎儿动静真大
Oh, the baby's really moving now.

156
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:04,190
宝宝在踢  你想摸摸看吗
It's kicking. Do you want to feel?

157
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,950
不用了  谢谢
No, thank you.

158
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:08,540
这感觉真奇妙
Such a strange feeling.

159
00:12:12,490 --> 00:12:14,990
要对另一个生命负责
To be wholly responsible for the life of another.

160
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:19,560
我还听说  等你有了孩子
Also, I hear, when you have kids, you never...

161
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:22,420
就没法像以前一样睡觉了
sleep quite the same again.

162
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:27,520
痛苦分两种
There are two kinds of pain.

163
00:12:31,860 --> 00:12:34,410
道格·斯坦普给我发了条信息
Doug Stamper sent me that text,

164
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,290
他说这是你丈夫日记里的话
he said it comes from your husband's diary.

165
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:43,410
我要问你
Now, I ask you,

166
00:12:44,580 --> 00:12:48,600
我该采访你  还是他
who should I interview, you or him?

167
00:12:52,140 --> 00:12:53,450
我知道你们有些人过来
I know that some of you are here

168
00:12:53,450 --> 00:12:54,420
是因为不确定
because you're not sure 

169
00:12:54,420 --> 00:12:56,890
明年的聚会我是否还会健在
I'm gonna be around at next year's gathering.

170
00:12:57,050 --> 00:12:58,920
没事  我从你们的表情里
Oh, no, no, I can see it on--

171
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:01,370
看得出  没错
On your faces. And it's true.

172
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:06,240
过去几个月  我反思了一下
These last few months, I've had to look back.

173
00:13:07,660 --> 00:13:10,870
但我很兴奋  真的
But I'm excited. I am.

174
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,780
正如我妹妹所言
As my sister told you,

175
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:18,190
这个国家接下来几个月会迎来改变
there are changes coming to this country in the next few months.

176
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:21,640
我为之努力了20多年
The kind that I haven't been able to accomplish

177
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:24,440
依然没有实现
in the 20 plus years that I've been at it.

178
