00:37:26,030 --> 00:37:27,380
我们正在审理的案子
We are considering a case

542
00:37:27,380 --> 00:37:30,890
能直接影响到总统职位
that will directly affect the office of the presidency.

543
00:37:30,930 --> 00:37:35,370
我知道  一个以布雷特参与签署的重要法案
I know, a case based on the monumental piece of legislation

544
00:37:35,370 --> 00:37:37,210
为基础的案子
co-signed by Brett.

545
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:39,980
但我们三个今天碰面
But the three of us standing here right now

546
00:37:39,980 --> 00:37:41,530
跟那无关
have nothing to do with that.

547
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:44,330
对不对  议员
Isn't that right, Congressman?

548
00:37:46,020 --> 00:37:47,420
对  总统女士
Yes, Madam President.

549
00:37:48,970 --> 00:37:50,480
我会让议长解释的
I'll let the speaker explain.

550
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:52,820
因为有几项选择供你考虑
'Cause you have a number of options to consider.

551
00:37:53,270 --> 00:37:56,350
我想让你知道这件事让我多尴尬
And I want you to know how truly embarrassing it is for me.

552
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:58,540
我为最高法院选的人竟要面对如此悲哀的命运
The sad fate of my choice for the court.

553
00:38:03,110 --> 00:38:06,990
另外  我爱尚普兰湖
And by the way, I love Lake Champlain.

554
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:09,150
我只去过两次
I've only been there twice,

555
00:38:09,150 --> 00:38:11,370
但我永远忘不了湖水溅在脚上的冰冷
but I'll never forget the thrilling shock

556
00:38:11,370 --> 00:38:13,340
是多刻骨铭心
of the cold water on my feet.

557
00:38:13,980 --> 00:38:17,670
我孙子得了多发性硬化症  他必须游泳
My grandson has MS. He needs to swim.

558
00:38:18,590 --> 00:38:21,730
我不妄作评论  阿布佐法官
I don't judge, Justice Abruzzo.

559
00:38:22,970 --> 00:38:26,060
不对  除了对谎话
I'll correct that. Except for mendacity.

560
00:38:27,120 --> 00:38:29,020
我没法支持谎话
That I can't support.

561
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:34,230
还有  布雷特  你跟谢泼德兄妹汇报时
And, Brett, when you report this back to the Shepherds,

562
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:37,040
替我代好
give them my best.

563
00:38:43,650 --> 00:38:46,070
{\an7}谢泼德堂
舞蹈中心

564
00:38:43,950 --> 00:38:45,540
作为谢泼德家族的一员  你知道自己有责任
As a Shepherd, you know it's your duty to

565
00:38:45,540 --> 00:38:48,350
回报艺术事业  回报你所在的社区
give back to the arts and the communities you're involved in.

566
00:38:48,670 --> 00:38:51,150
我们在加德纳分析做的一切
You know, everything we've ever done at Gardner Analytics

567
00:38:51,150 --> 00:38:52,390
都是为了服务用户
is to serve the user.

568
00:38:52,400 --> 00:38:54,260
你已经说的很清楚了  没错
You've made that clear, yes.

569
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:56,090
但你知道用户授权给了你们
And yet, you were aware of the amount of data

570
00:38:56,090 --> 00:38:58,390
多少数据
the user was essentially signing over to you.

571
00:38:58,080 --> 00:39:07,760
{\an1}{\pos(120.3,232)}邓肯·谢泼德
回应应用软件读取隐私信息的指控

572
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:00,220
并不比其他应用多
No more than any other application.

573
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:01,170
但白宫声称
But the White House is saying

574
00:39:01,170 --> 00:39:02,800
谢泼德自由基金会应用
that the Shepherd Freedom Foundation app

575
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:04,650
比其他应用更过分
went beyond any other application.

576
00:39:04,780 --> 00:39:06,140
它让国会竞选团队
That it allowed congressional campaigns

577
00:39:06,140 --> 00:39:08,330
获得用户手机的全部权限
complete access to the user's phone.

578
00:39:08,330 --> 00:39:09,350
有人甚至说
Some are even saying that

579
00:39:09,350 --> 00:39:11,840
这款应用能操控人的精神
the app is essentially mining peoples' psyches.

580
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:14,620
是这样
Look.

581
00:39:14,650 --> 00:39:16,590
我们设计了应用
You design the thing, but at the end of the day,

582
00:39:16,590 --> 00:39:18,780
但无从知道人们会怎么使用它
you have no idea how it will be used.

583
00:39:18,780 --> 00:39:19,530
谢泼德先生
Mr. Shepherd.

584
00:39:21,780 --> 00:39:23,840
我能失陪一下吗
Could you excuse me for one moment, please?

585
00:39:26,660 --> 00:39:28,480
我是联调局的斯雷特探员
I'm Agent Slater with the FBI.

586
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:31,650
有什么事吗
What's this about?

587
00:39:31,650 --> 00:39:32,500
请跟我们来一趟
Please come with us.

588
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:34,390
在通知律师之前我哪也不去
I'm not going anywhere until I call my lawyer.

589
00:39:34,390 --> 00:39:35,940
谢泼德先生  请吧
Mr. Shepherd, please.

590
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,980
你最好配合一点
It'd be best if you cooperated.

591
00:39:44,180 --> 00:39:46,550
阿布鲁佐正申请回避
Abruzzo is recusing himself.

592
00:39:46,720 --> 00:39:48,080
为什么
On what grounds?

593
00:39:48,670 --> 00:39:50,140
利益冲突
His conflict of interest.

594
00:39:51,140 --> 00:39:53,780
这可事关总统之位的未来
This is about the future of the presidency.

595
00:39:53,790 --> 00:39:55,680
他用自己在部队服役的事当借口
He's using his military service.

596
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:58,220
把他叫过来
Get him over here.

597
00:39:58,820 --> 00:40:01,680
太迟了  他不能撤回申请了
It's too late, he can't reverse himself.

598
00:40:01,680 --> 00:40:03,950
迟不迟由我来定
I decide when it's too late.

599
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:06,140
我不会让这个裁决通过的
I will not have that ruling upheld.

600
00:40:06,690 --> 00:40:07,900
我们还能去找谁
Who else can we get to?

601
00:40:11,220 --> 00:40:11,900
巴里
Barry.

602
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:14,480
安奈特  别开电视
Annette, do not turn on the TV.

603
00:40:15,100 --> 00:40:16,390
你在说什么
What are you talking about?

604
00:40:16,620 --> 00:40:19,250
他们把他带走了  他们带着逮捕证闯了进来
They took him. They came in with a warrant.

605
00:40:20,170 --> 00:40:21,580
你说他被带走了是什么意思
What do you mean they took him?

606
00:40:21,580 --> 00:40:23,040
他们以应用为由
They're using his work with the app

607
00:40:23,050 --> 00:40:24,850
控诉他犯有叛国罪
as grounds to charge him with treason.

608
00:40:24,850 --> 00:40:27,360
我向你保证  我们会极尽所能去救他
I promise you, we will do everything we can.

609
00:40:27,410 --> 00:40:28,790
但所有与这款应用有牵连的人
But anyone connected with the app

610
00:40:28,790 --> 00:40:31,850
都在和它  还有你撇清关系
is distancing themselves from it and you.

611
00:40:37,980 --> 00:40:39,380
这一刻终于来了
It's finally here.

612
00:40:47,070 --> 00:40:48,520
稿子都是谁改的
Where did these changes come from?

613
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:50,300
谢泼德家族直接改的
Directly from the Shepherd family.

614
00:40:51,220 --> 00:40:52,000
是他妈妈吗
His mother?

615
00:40:52,390 --> 00:40:54,820
只管做好你的工作  开始录像吧
Look, just do your thing. Let's get it on tape.

616
00:41:01,180 --> 00:41:03,220
纳粹一般的策略
Nazi-like tactics?

617
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:05,760
除非话题有关二战
You bring up Nazis in any situation

618
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:07,350
不然你一提起纳粹
other than the Second World War,

619
00:41:07,350 --> 00:41:09,020
就已经输掉辩论了
you've already lost the argument.

620
00:41:09,020 --> 00:41:11,780
得了吧  我们都知道邓肯干了什么
I mean, come on, we all knew what Duncan was doing.

621
00:41:11,840 --> 00:41:13,600
还有谁没料到吗
Is anybody really surprised?

622
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:15,130
-认真的吗  -梅乐蒂
- I mean, really? - Melody...

623
00:41:22,550 --> 00:41:23,280
怎么了
What?

624
00:41:25,300 --> 00:41:26,770
-你这是  -不干了
- What are you-- - No.

625
00:41:29,100 --> 00:41:30,720
民调显示她的支持率达75%以上
She's polling in the high 70s.

626
00:41:30,720 --> 00:41:33,710
到中期选举时可能达到近80%
We're looking at close to 80 by the midterms.

627
00:41:33,790 --> 00:41:35,680
反企业浪潮
The anti-corporate rant

628
00:41:35,680 --> 00:41:36,980
也在愈演愈烈
is gaining traction.

629
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:39,170
她在拿女权主义当武器
She's weaponized her feminism,

630
00:41:39,830 --> 00:41:41,400
这让人越来越厌烦
and it's grown tiresome.

631
00:41:42,250 --> 00:41:44,070
"我是个母亲  也是个将军"
"I'm a mother, I'm a general."

632
00:41:44,770 --> 00:41:45,710
拉倒吧
Spare me.

633
00:41:46,020 --> 00:41:48,790
像她这么受欢迎的人对民主是有害的
Anyone that popular is bad for democracy.

634
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:51,190
马克
Mark.

635
00:41:51,900 --> 00:41:53,190
先说有利之处
So, the pros.

636
00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:57,480
她死后  副总统的位子空缺
After her death, with the vice presidency vacant,

637
00:41:58,810 --> 00:42:00,840
我们的朋友布雷特·柯尔会成为总统
our friend Brett Cole will be president.

638
00:42:01,270 --> 00:42:06,360
我们猜想到时人们会呼吁安定和团结
We suspect we'll get a call for stability and unity.

639
00:42:07,810 --> 00:42:09,950
治愈这个国家  套路大家都清楚
Heal the nation, we all know the drill.

640
00:42:10,890 --> 00:42:13,240
不利之处是  我们会在中期选举受到打击
The cons. We're gonna take a hit in the midterms.

641
00:42:13,740 --> 00:42:15,270
我觉得众议院还能保住
I think we hold on to the House.

642
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:17,110
参议院就难说了
The Senate is a long shot.

643
00:42:18,020 --> 00:42:21,040
市场会波动一段时间
The markets will fluctuate for a while.

644
00:42:21,050 --> 00:42:23,040
为此我叫了洛琳来
I've brought Lorraine in for that.

645
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:24,110
她做了一些很不错的
She's got some impressive

646
00:42:24,110 --> 00:42:26,430
计算机模型和预测
computer models and projections. But...

647
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:29,410
总而言之  我们有信心承受
all in all, we're confident we can absorb

648
00:42:29,410 --> 00:42:30,850
刺杀所能引发的
whatever financial hit

649
00:42:30,860 --> 00:42:33,110
经济波动所导致的金融损失
an assassination would have on the economy.

650
00:42:33,550 --> 00:42:35,560
GDP总值可能最多会损失
We're talking about a quarter point loss

651
00:42:35,570 --> 00:42:37,680
四分之一个百分点
in the GDP, at the most.

652
00:42:38,050 --> 00:42:41,140
那可能引发的阴谋论呢
And what about all the conspiracy nonsense we'll be hearing?

653
00:42:41,410 --> 00:42:44,100
这些论调可以分散人们的注意力
The theories are a useful distraction.

654
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:46,700
最终都会不了了之
And eventually, they consume themselves.

655
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:48,400
这在历史上有先例可循
History will back us up on that.

656
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:50,340
还有个重大的障碍
There's one hiccup. It's a big one.

657
00:42:52,230 --> 00:42:53,550
她怀了孩子
She's with child.

658
00:42:53,950 --> 00:42:56,660
这是一个我们不知道如何
That is a variable we don't know

659
00:42:56,660 --> 00:42:59,230
在我们的模型中计算或预测的变量
how to account for in our models or predict.

660
00:42:59,230 --> 00:43:02,310
我们要利用它
We use it. Play into it.

661
00:43:02,960 --> 00:43:04,350
我们要让她成为烈士
We'll make her a martyr.

662
00:43:05,250 --> 00:43:06,730
时代的牺牲品
A victim of the times.

663
00:43:07,010 --> 00:43:08,680
女权主义的偶像
A feminist icon.

664
00:43:09,700 --> 00:43:13,210
天哪  她甚至可能被印到硬币上
God, she might even end up on a coin.

665
00:43:14,060 --> 00:43:16,620
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}意外拍摄到肯尼迪被刺杀场景的路人

666
00:43:14,060 --> 00:43:16,620
只要不再出现一个泽普鲁德
As long as another Zapruder doesn't show up.

667
00:43:16,940 --> 00:43:18,100
杰克  这不好笑
Jack, that's not funny.

668
00:43:19,630 --> 00:43:22,400
我想知道的就这么多
Well, that's as much as I want to know.

669
00:43:23,830 --> 00:43:25,930
是的  我想你们最好现在就走吧
Yes, I think it's best if you all leave now.

670
00:43:26,570 --> 00:43:27,550
接下来交给我
I'll take it from here.

671
00:43:38,650 --> 00:43:39,410
把他带进来
Bring him in.

672
00:44:26,890 --> 00:44:28,980
到最后关头了
It's 11 o'clock, as they say.

673
00:44:32,870 --> 00:44:34,240
你想要我手里的东西
You want what I have.

674
00:44:36,570 --> 00:44:38,940
事实上  我希望你继续拿着
Actually, I want you to hold on to it.

675
00:44:40,010 --> 00:44:42,670
我告诉过赛斯  我再告诉你一次
I told Seth, and I'll tell you again.

676
00:44:43,610 --> 00:44:46,770
我想把她搞垮  而不是弗兰西斯
I want to bring her down, but not Francis.

677
00:44:47,460 --> 00:44:49,230
难道你不知道那是不可能的吗
Don't you know that's impossible?

678
00:44:49,900 --> 00:44:51,410
即使杀她丈夫的人就是她
Even if she killed her husband?

679
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:52,740
道格...
Doug...

680
00:44:53,940 --> 00:44:56,660
我们两个的目标是一致的
my goal and yours have become the same.

681
00:44:59,220 --> 00:45:00,630
她叫你道格吗
Does she call you Doug?

682
00:45:01,780 --> 00:45:04,150
还是像她叫弗兰西斯一样
Or does she do that Francis thing of hers.

683
00:45:05,840 --> 00:45:06,750
道格拉斯
Douglas.

684
00:45:07,560 --> 00:45:09,340
你知道我们需要做什么
You know what we need to do.

685
00:45:09,430 --> 00:45:11,790
你总是把我想错
You keep mistaking me for someone I'm not.

686
00:45:12,920 --> 00:45:14,920
我不在乎你  也不在乎你想要什么
I don't care about you or what you want.

687
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,740
但你确实在乎弗兰克想要什么
But you do care what Frank wanted.

688
00:45:17,520 --> 00:45:19,170
现在你该承认了
And it's time you admitted it.

689
00:45:19,510 --> 00:45:21,320
弗兰克想让她死
Frank wanted her dead.

690
00:45:23,300 --> 00:45:24,890
这对你来说似乎更像是私人恩怨
This seems too personal for you.

691
00:45:24,890 --> 00:45:27,180
所有政治都是私人恩怨
All politics is personal.

692
00:45:27,420 --> 00:45:29,140
你是最该知道这一点的人
You of all people know that.

693
00:45:30,380 --> 00:45:31,950
你也希望她死
And you want her dead, too.

694
00:45:33,500 --> 00:45:35,470
我们两个人都不能单独做成这件事
And neither one of us can do it alone.

695
00:45:47,600 --> 00:45:49,310
你很快就会想明白的
You'll come to your senses soon.

696
00:45:51,050 --> 00:45:51,800
你不是傻瓜
You're no fool.

697
00:45:53,230 --> 00:45:55,150
你想保护他留给你的东西吗
You want to protect what he left you?

698
00:45:55,900 --> 00:45:56,910
这是唯一的办法
It's the only way.

699
00:46:11,990 --> 00:46:14,860
我要为法院即将做出的判决祝贺你
Congratulations on the ruling coming out of the court.

700
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:16,540
他们还没有决定
They still haven't decided.

701
00:46:16,540 --> 00:46:18,350
但我们都知道结果会如何
But we all know how it's going to go.

702
00:46:20,830 --> 00:46:21,650
请坐
Please, sit down.

703
00:46:25,340 --> 00:46:26,680
诺拉·卡弗蒂...
Nora Cafferty...

704
00:46:27,800 --> 00:46:29,010
有一个秘密
has a secret.

705
00:46:30,790 --> 00:46:31,530
您说什么
Excuse me.

706
00:46:32,760 --> 00:46:35,490
我以为你是在担心胎儿的事
I assume you were worried about the scare with the baby.

707
00:46:36,790 --> 00:46:38,350
我跟佩特罗夫总统谈过
I spoke to President Petrov.

708
00:46:38,350 --> 00:46:39,330
他告诉我
He's informed me that

709
00:46:39,330 --> 00:46:43,210
哈里发国正在试图获取核设备
ICO is trying to acquire a nuclear device.

710
00:46:44,320 --> 00:46:46,430
对  确实
Yes. They are.

711
00:46:46,430 --> 00:46:48,220
那你为什么没告诉我
So why didn't you tell me?

712
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:53,050
我完全信任你  诺拉
I have full confidence in you, Nora,

713
00:46:53,050 --> 00:46:55,360
也信任你的能力  但这让我担心
and your abilities, but this concerns me.

714
00:46:56,870 --> 00:46:59,720
你在任何情况下都不能
You cannot under any circumstances

715
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:03,380
隐瞒对我们国家安全至关重要的信息
withhold information that is essential to our national security.

716
00:47:05,760 --> 00:47:07,600
我曾对你有很高的期待
I had such high hopes for you.

717
00:47:08,670 --> 00:47:09,480
你说什么
I'm sorry.

718
00:47:13,440 --> 00:47:15,180
我本不想把这话说出来
I didn't want to have to say this.

719
00:47:16,690 --> 00:47:19,310
我本希望最高法院的判决对你不利
I was hoping the Supreme Court would rule against you.

720
00:47:19,840 --> 00:47:21,410
希望他们剥夺你控制核武的权利
That they would take away the football.

721
00:47:22,460 --> 00:47:24,770
我不是唯一一个开始有这种感觉的人
And I'm not the only one who's starting to feel it.

722
00:47:29,820 --> 00:47:32,800
这是我的地盘  我要你出去
This is my house, and I want you out.

